<title type="html"><![CDATA[sbc instruction question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=604&amp;p=4962#p4962"><![CDATA[
The sbc instruction does a subtract with borrow, which is the logical negation of a carry. So if the C flag is clear, an additional #01 will be subtracted. Use sec before the sbc instruction to remove the borrow.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=190">kingshriek</a> — Tue Sep 27, 2005 10:37 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
